</div></span><span class='ContentPaneDiv3'><div id="_ctrl0_ctl39_divModuleContainer" class="module module-details module-news-details container">
    <div class="module_container module_container--outer">
        
       
        <div class="module_container module_container--inner">
            <h2 class="module-details_title">
                <span id="_ctrl0_ctl39_lblModuleDetailHeadline">Altria Releases Its Inaugural Task Force on Climate-Related Financial Disclosures Report</span>
            </h2>
            <div class="module_container module_container--content">
                <div class="module_date-time">
                    <span id="_ctrl0_ctl39_lblDate" class="module_date-text">11/16/2021</span>
                </div>
                <div class="module_links module_q4-icon-links">
                    <div class="module_related-document">
                        <a id="_ctrl0_ctl39_hrefDownload" class="module_link module_news-details_download" target="_blank" style="DISPLAY:none;">
                            <span id="_ctrl0_ctl39_lblDownload" class="module_link-text">Download this Press Release</span>
                            <span class="sr-only">PDF Format (opens in new window)</span>
                            <span id="_ctrl0_ctl39_lblDocument" class="module_file-size"></span>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <div class="module_body">
                    <style type="text/css">.q4default .bwalignc { text-align: center; list-style-position: inside }.q4default .bwlistdisc { list-style-type: disc }.q4default .bwuline { text-decoration: underline }</style><div class="q4default"><p>    RICHMOND, Va.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--
Altria Group, Inc. (“Altria”) (NYSE:MO) today announces its first standalone Task Force on Climate-related Financial Disclosures (TCFD) <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fcorporate-responsibility-reports%2Ftcfd-report.pdf&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=report&amp;index=1&amp;md5=68d034ba11711a9d4ee0836c90e6eeb2" shape="rect">report</a>. Altria is proud to be the first U.S tobacco company to join more than 2,700 supporters of the TCFD. The TCFD was formed by the Financial Stability Board in 2015 to help companies provide decision-useful information about their climate-related risks and opportunities to investors. In 2017, the TCFD published final recommendations across four core elements: governance, strategy, risk management, and metrics and targets.
</p><p>
“Just as we believe in the benefits of a science- and evidence-based approach for our industry and tobacco harm reduction, we believe in a science-based approach for climate action,” said Sal Mancuso, Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Financial Officer. “We also acknowledge this is our first TCFD report and expectations for Environmental, Social and Governance disclosure are rapidly changing. We intend to learn as we go while responding to this dynamic environment as we evolve our reporting in the future.”
</p><p>
Altria’s support for the TCFD is consistent with its commitment to transparency. This year, Altria disclosed its progress and key metrics for each of its responsibility focus areas:
</p><ul class="bwlistdisc">
  <li>
    <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fcorporate-responsibility-reports%2Fprotect-the-environment-2020-2021.pdf&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Protect+the+Environment&amp;index=2&amp;md5=2d4605dc882b24b0fe630c4c18ab2bab" shape="rect">Protect the Environment</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fcorporate-responsibility-reports%2Freducing-harm-and-preventing-underage-use-2020-2021.pdf&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Reducing+Harm+and+Preventing+Underage+Use&amp;index=3&amp;md5=0ea73972a4b050a1f5069a5188380824" shape="rect">Reducing Harm and Preventing Underage Use</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fcorporate-responsibility-reports%2Fdrive-responsibility-through-our-value-chain-2020-2021.pdf%3Fsrc%3Dcorporate-responsibility-reports&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Drive+Responsibility+Through+Our+Value+Chain&amp;index=4&amp;md5=84841f4e36146ecb67dba4839739d4d3" shape="rect">Drive Responsibility Through Our Value Chain</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fcorporate-responsibility-reports%2Fsupport-our-people-and-communities-2020-2021.pdf%3Fsrc%3Dcorporate-responsibility-reports&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Supporting+Our+People+%26amp%3B+Communities&amp;index=5&amp;md5=adb4319d9b612d2d24cd81eabad951a5" shape="rect">Supporting Our People &amp; Communities</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fat-a-glance%2Ffocus-areas-and-goals%2F2020-2021-cr-engage-and-lead-responsibly-report.pdf%3Fsrc%3Dcorporate-responsibility-reports&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Engage+%26amp%3B+Lead+Responsibly&amp;index=6&amp;md5=366ef402a3cbce05543772f8477afad0" shape="rect">Engage &amp; Lead Responsibly</a>
  </li>
</ul><p>
Altria’s responsibility focus areas are guided by its <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAltria%2FAltria%2Fresponsibility%2Fat-a-glance%2Ffocus-areas-and-goals%2F2020-2021-cr-engage-and-lead-responsibly-report.pdf%3Fsrc%3D2025-responsibility-focus-areas-and-goals%23page%3D12&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=materiality+assessment&amp;index=7&amp;md5=34789c076bb129f39197359984ae1165" shape="rect">materiality assessment </a>process – a comprehensive, formal approach to identify the most impactful ESG issues that Altria believes are important to its long-term sustainability and success.
</p><p>
Altria has made a strong commitment to reducing <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com%2Fresponsibility%2Fprotect-the-environment%3Fsrc%3D2025-focus-areas-goals&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=its+environmental+impact&amp;index=8&amp;md5=65b707852537d97e448b762cd0586d76" shape="rect">its environmental impact</a>, both in its companies' direct operations and in the value chain (from supplier to retailer).
</p><p>
For more information about the TCFD, please visit <a href="http://www.fsb-tcfd.org">www.fsb-tcfd.org</a>.
</p><p>
  <b>
    <span class="bwuline">Altria’s Profile
</span>
  </b>
  <br>Altria has a leading portfolio of tobacco products for U.S. tobacco consumers age 21+. Altria’s Vision by 2030 is to responsibly lead the transition of adult smokers to a smoke-free future (Vision). Altria is <i>Moving Beyond Smoking</i>™, leading the way in moving adult smokers away from cigarettes by taking action to transition millions to potentially less harmful choices - believing it is a substantial opportunity for adult tobacco consumers, Altria’s businesses and society.
</p><p>
Altria’s wholly owned subsidiaries include the most profitable tobacco companies in their categories: Philip Morris USA Inc. (PM USA), U.S. Smokeless Tobacco Company LLC (USSTC) and John Middleton Co. (Middleton). Altria’s smoke-free portfolio includes Helix Innovations LLC (Helix), the maker of <i>on!</i> oral nicotine pouches, exclusive U.S. commercialization rights to the <i>IQOS Tobacco Heating System</i>® and <i>Marlboro HeatSticks</i>®, and an equity investment in JUUL Labs, Inc. (JUUL).
</p><p>
Altria also owns equity investments in Anheuser-Busch InBev SA/NV (ABI), the world’s largest brewer, and Cronos Group Inc. (Cronos), a leading Canadian cannabinoid company.
</p><p>
The brand portfolios of Altria’s tobacco operating companies include <i>Marlboro</i><sup>®</sup>, <i>Black &amp; Mild</i><sup>®</sup>, <i>Copenhagen</i><sup>®</sup>, <i>Skoal</i><sup>®</sup> and <i>on!</i><sup>®</sup>. Trademarks and service marks related to Altria referenced in this release are the property of Altria or its subsidiaries or are used with permission.
</p><p>
Learn more about Altria at <a rel="nofollow" href="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.altria.com&amp;esheet=52531242&amp;newsitemid=20211116005917&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=www.altria.com&amp;index=9&amp;md5=53637f6483cc245d14a22c03a72d70a4" shape="rect">www.altria.com</a> and follow us on Twitter, Facebook and LinkedIn.
</p><p>
  <img alt="" src="https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=bwnews&amp;sty=20211116005917r1&amp;sid=acqr8&amp;distro=nx&amp;lang=en" style="width:0;height:0">
  <span class="bwct31415"></span>
</p><p id="mmgallerylink">
  <span id="mmgallerylink-phrase">View source version on <a href="http://businesswire.com">businesswire.com</a>: </span>
  <span id="mmgallerylink-link">
